# Test Execution

All tests (unit or integration) must be run inside the dev container.

## Entering the container

```bash
python3 tools/dev.py          # builds image on first run (~20-30 min)
python3 tools/dev.py --rebuild  # force image rebuild
```

The workspace is mounted at `/workspace` inside the container.

## Running tests

```bash
# boot integration test
cd /workspace/tests/boot && make clean && make gen_config && make run

# context switch integration test
cd /workspace/tests/ctx_switch && make clean && make gen_config && make run

# context switch stress test
cd /workspace/tests/ctx_switch && make clean && make gen_config && make stress
```

## Rules
- Never run tests directly on the host — the TriCore toolchain and QEMU AURIX fork are only available inside the container.
- Always run `make gen_config` before building if `ul/config.h` may be stale.
- When adding a new test, provide a `Makefile` with `gen_config`, `all`, `run`, and `clean` targets following the same pattern as existing tests.
